@adstrakt maybe there will be some minor change as the privacy option, opting for a Z tx instead of a T one on compatible chains will require 2 checkboxes instead of one, instead of "I want it private", I believe each side should have : I want to pay in Z AND I want to be paid in Z checkboxes.

For the behaviour, the :"I want to pay in Z" will only be a checkbox that will activate a db flag to let scripts know they have to gen a Z, no ui work, just the checkbox.
the : "I want to be paid in Z" will have just a slight modification : src_deal must be checked accordingly, as the receiving address won't be a T anymore
